      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRATHIE KIRK (3) exciting filly resuming for her second campaign. Stepped up in trip at her third race start with a slashing Maiden victory over 1400m at Scone last November. Wasn't pushed out in her two trials and finds a winnable race to kick off. Go close. SHOUTABOUTIT (2) gets a better set-up today after going back from the wide gate with a battling eighth over 1100m at Hawkesbury in BM64 grade. Can stalk the speed here and figure prominently. TIDES TURNING (1) holding her form with the two minor placings over the shorter trip. Maps well with the claim and not to be underestimated in this weaker contest. OFCOURSEIAM (4) lone victory came at this trip and deep into the campaign from the better draw. Chipped away late with a handy fourth over 1190m at Grafton. Worth thought.",
